# Localization Maintenance

- Keep all supported app languages in sync for non-legacy, non-quiz user-facing flows
- Legacy flow pages and quiz pages are intentionally excluded from localization for the small pre-selected-user group
- Default language from the browser language when no explicit saved preference exists: use the supported browser locale when available, otherwise English
- Persist explicit language changes from settings on the client
- Store translation resources in-repo behind one shared localization layer
- Prefer split per-locale modules with lazy loading as supported languages grow
- Keep common software actions and statuses in shared translation keys; keep page namespaces for contextual copy only
- When changing user-facing copy in localized areas, update every supported locale in the same change
- When UI copy, toasts, or feature branches are removed, remove the corresponding dead translation keys from every supported locale in the same change
